{"ts":"2026-06-27T16:44:29.290Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"done","reason":"completed","text":"Submission recorded (verified): ### 1. Files Changed\n- **Next.js App Router (TypeScript)**:\n  - `app/api/v1/support/route.ts` (Updated list and create APIs with advanced filtering, scoping, and standard payload mapping)\n  - `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts` (Updated retrieval by ID, added PATCH update API, and updated comment handler with dual-layer checks)\n  - `app/api/v1/support/[id]/status/route.ts` (Created new status update endpoint)\n  - `app/api/v1/support/[id]/assign/route.ts` (Created new ticket assignment endpoint)\n\n- **FastAPI Backend (Python)**:\n  - `backend/app/models/support_ticket.py` (Added `comments` string/text column to SQLAlchemy model to persist comment threads)\n  - `backend/app/schemas/support_ticket.py` (Added `comments` field validation on Pydantic create, update, and response schemas)\n  - `backend/app/api/routes/support_tickets.py` (Created CRUD API endpoints: GET list with query filtering, GET by ID, POST create, PATCH update, PATCH status, PATCH assign, and POST comment, with full role-based access control and tenant isolation checks)\n\n### 2. Summary of Implementation\n- **Robust Scoping & RBAC**: Implemented strict tenant security. Platform administrators and support agents can see, manage, and assign any ticket. Clients can only see, create, and comment on tickets associated with their specific client account.\n- **Advanced Filtering**: Added support for filtering by `status`, `priority`, `category`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `assigned_to`, and a multi-field `search` query across both routers.\n- **Fields Mapping**: Supported standard client fields (`title`, `description`, `category`, `priority`, `status`, `client_id`, `project_id`, `assigned_to`, `created_by`) and mapped them bi-directionally to existing UI structures to prevent frontend breakage.\n- **Comment Persistence**: Added serialized comment storage inside the FastAPI SQLite engine, tracking commenter identity and timestamp.\n\n### 3. Validation Done\n- Ran `npm run backend:seed` which successfully drop-rebuilt and seeded the SQLite schema with comments support.\n- Ran `npm run backend:check` which executed both RBAC security dependency tests and API smoke tests, passing 100% of cases.\n- Validated TypeScript compiling cleanly on the newly created Next.js routes.\n\n### 4. Limitations\n- Front-end only placeholders are used for advanced email sending or upload attachments, as backend/third-party dependencies are skipped in accordance with project guardrails.","iterations":63,"usage":{"inputTokens":4402052,"outputTokens":55693,"cacheReadTokens":3852955,"totalCost":1.9028257499999999}}}
